"Highest-priority comment:
Monsters and chests overwrite floor tiles in the grid (using TILE_MONSTER/TILE_CHEST), but the requirement states the character can move only on floor tiles. This also weakens the “always at least one valid path” guarantee if later you enforce floor-only passability. Entities should be overlays on top of floor tiles, not tile types.

How to fix:
- Treat monsters and chests as entities placed on floor cells; never change the base grid from FLOOR for them.
- Use the monsters dict and chests set to detect encounters; keep the grid limited to WALL/FLOOR/DOOR for passability.

Concretely:
